xactly k elements.\n3. The top of the heap will be the kth largest element.','kth-largest-element-in-an-array','class Solution {\npublic:\n    int findKthLargest(vector<int>& nums, int k) {\n        // Your code here\n        return 0;\n    }\n};','class Solution {\n    public int findKthLargest(int[] nums, int k) {\n        // Your code here\n        return 0;\n    }\n}','class Solution:\n    def findKthLargest(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        # Your code here\n        return 0','[{\"input\":\"1 1 1 1\\n1\",\"expectedOutput\":\"1\",\"explanation\":\"All elements are equal, so the kth largest remains the same.\"},{\"input\":\"2 2 3 1\\n3\",\"expectedOutput\":\"2\",\"explanation\":\"Duplicate values should still yield the correct kth largest.\"},{\"input\":\"7 6 5 4 3 2 1\\n7\",\"expectedOutput\":\"1\",\"explanation\":\"The smallest element is the 7th largest in a seven-element array.\"},{\"input\":\"5 4 3 2 1\\n5\",\"expectedOutput\":\"1\",\"explanation\":\"The array minimum becomes the kth largest when k equals length.\"},{\"input\":\"2 1 2 1 2 1\\n2\",\"expectedOutput\":\"2\",\"explanation\":\"Kth largest with repeated values should handle duplicates.\"}]',NULL,NULL,'[{\"input\":\"3 2 1 5 6 4\\n2\",\"expectedOutput\":\"5\",\"explanation\":\"The second largest number in the array.\"},{\"input\":\"3 2 3 1 2 4 5 5 6\\n4\",\"expectedOutput\":\"4\",\"explanation\":\"Select the fourth largest element correctly.\"}]'),(9,0,0,'STACK_QUEUE','2026-05-23 03:29:22.831395','You are given an array of integers nums, there is a sliding window of size k which is moving from the very left of the array to the very right. You can only see the k numbers in the window. Each time the sliding window moves right by one position.\n\nReturn the max sliding window.','HARD','Input: nums = [1,3,-1,-3,5,3,6,7], k = 3\nOutput: [3,3,5,5,6,7]\n\nInput: nums = [1], k = 1\nOutput: [1]','[3,3,5,5,6,7] / [1]','Implement the algorithm using interview patterns and careful edge case handli